==English==
===Etymology===
From ''[[a-]]'' "on" + Old English ''baft'', ''baften'', ''biaften'', Anglo Saxon ''beæftan''; ''be'' "by" + ''æftan'' "behind". See [[After]], [[Aft]], [[By]]

===Preposition===
#''(nautical):'' [[Behind]]; toward the [[stern]] [[relative]] to some other [[object]] or [[position]]; as, ''abaft'' the [[wheelhouse]].

====Phrases====
*'''Abaft the [[beam]]''': to one side and behind an [[imaginary]] line drawn across the centre of a ship.

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[takana]], [[peräpuolella]]
*German: [[achter]], [[hinter]]

